Now I understand the bug. In the buggy kernel, `balance_push()` doesn't check `cpu_dying()`, so when the callback is installed (e.g., from stale hotplug state), it incorrectly pushes tasks off even when the CPU isn't dying. The fix adds a `cpu_dying()` check.

